WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.750
(metallic music)

00:00:11.480 --> 00:00:14.560
- Calculating the amount
of protein you need,

00:00:14.560 --> 00:00:15.420
is pretty simple.

00:00:15.420 --> 00:00:17.930
You need one gram per
pound of body weight,

00:00:17.930 --> 00:00:19.500
and there's many research studies

00:00:19.500 --> 00:00:21.870
have driven this conclusion.

00:00:21.870 --> 00:00:23.250
One gram per pound of body weight

00:00:23.250 --> 00:00:26.760
or 2.2 gram per kilogram of body weight.

00:00:26.760 --> 00:00:31.760
All of this research was
done, with standard sources

00:00:32.830 --> 00:00:34.710
not including fortagen.

00:00:34.710 --> 00:00:36.580
So it was done with whey protein,

00:00:36.580 --> 00:00:37.970
or it was done with meats

00:00:37.970 --> 00:00:40.510
or whatever somebody was eating in a day

00:00:40.510 --> 00:00:42.390
and there's many studies on this.

00:00:42.390 --> 00:00:46.950
So I see people looking at
the fact that meats only have

00:00:46.950 --> 00:00:50.680
38% of absorbability.

00:00:50.680 --> 00:00:54.040
So they only count 38% of the grams

00:00:54.040 --> 00:00:57.011
of protein towards their, you know,

00:00:57.011 --> 00:00:58.630
what they get in their day.

00:00:58.630 --> 00:00:59.900
You don't need to do that.

00:00:59.900 --> 00:01:01.140
Don't do that.

00:01:01.140 --> 00:01:03.520
So calculate the amount of grams you need

00:01:03.520 --> 00:01:05.570
like so let's say you weigh 200 pounds,

00:01:05.570 --> 00:01:07.970
you need 200 grams of protein,

00:01:07.970 --> 00:01:10.620
then if you want to be
at a caloric deficit

00:01:10.620 --> 00:01:14.170
so remember being in a
caloric deficit usually means

00:01:14.170 --> 00:01:15.450
you're at a protein deficit too

00:01:15.450 --> 00:01:17.090
and that's a way to lose muscle.

00:01:17.090 --> 00:01:18.720
If you're at a chloric deficit,

00:01:18.720 --> 00:01:22.140
but a protein match number
or a protein surplus,

00:01:22.140 --> 00:01:24.550
you're not gonna lose muscle,
but you will lose body fat.

00:01:24.550 --> 00:01:27.260
And that seems to be what
everybody's looking for.

00:01:27.260 --> 00:01:32.260
So what I do is, so I weigh 240 pounds

00:01:33.670 --> 00:01:38.290
so I try and get 200 grams of
protein through leaner meats.

00:01:38.290 --> 00:01:39.430
I'm going leaner now

00:01:39.430 --> 00:01:42.633
because I'm trying to be a leaner athlete,

00:01:43.750 --> 00:01:46.150
because I got sort of as big as

00:01:46.150 --> 00:01:48.304
I kinda ever really wanted to be.

00:01:48.304 --> 00:01:53.100
And, now I'm cutting cause
everybody has different goals

00:01:53.100 --> 00:01:57.130
so I used to eat like a
platter or rabbis every night.

00:01:57.130 --> 00:02:00.600
Now I'm eating like a platter of filets

00:02:00.600 --> 00:02:03.330
or New York steaks which were
much leaner cuts of meat.

00:02:03.330 --> 00:02:06.180
So, when I do my fortagen,

00:02:06.180 --> 00:02:07.730
I like doing two doses of it.

00:02:07.730 --> 00:02:10.090
I do one in the morning, one at night.

00:02:10.090 --> 00:02:13.280
So I can have it whenever but,

00:02:13.280 --> 00:02:16.890
so I get a hundred grams of
equivalent high quality protein

00:02:16.890 --> 00:02:18.133
from the fortagen,

00:02:19.140 --> 00:02:24.140
but then I get 200 grams
totaling 300 in a day

00:02:24.270 --> 00:02:26.370
because I wanna overshoot that number just

00:02:26.370 --> 00:02:29.930
to make sure that I'm
really going to be anabolic,

00:02:29.930 --> 00:02:33.763
while I sleep and I build a
considerable amount of muscle.

